DIGEST
SB 428 Original 2026 Regular Session Hensgens
Present law provides for rights of use, which are regulated by the rules of usufruct and
predial servitudes. Further provides that a predial servitude is a charge on a servient estate
for the benefit of a dominant estate.
Present law provides that a landowner may establish a pipeline servitude by contract.
Present law provides that a contract has the effect of law for the parties thereto and that the
obligations enumerated therein must be performed in good faith.
Proposed law retains present law and provides that laws governing usufruct and predial
servitudes cannot create additional obligations not stated in the contract.
Proposed law provides that proposed law is prospective and shall apply only to claims and
causes of action arising on or after the effective date.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 30:554.1)
